ch.uzh.agglorecommender.clusterer.treesearch

Class IndexAwareSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.uzh.agglorecommender.clusterer.treesearch.IndexAwareSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>

     class IndexAwareSet<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Set<E>, java.io.Serializable
    A set which allows accessing of elements by index. All added elements are also added to an internal list which is queried on an attempt to fetch an element by index. An element is only accessible if it is contained in the internal set.

    Beside the usual set methods the data structure provides three additional methods, namely:

    - E getByIndex(int index)
    - int getLastIndex()
    - int indexOf(E element)

    All set methods behave like the corresponding methods of java.util.HashSet with the following exceptions:

    - add(E e): addition of an element to the set adds the element also to the end of a list iff the list does not contain the element already.
    - addAll(Collection c): addition of multiple elements to the set adds each element also to the end of a list iff the list does not contain the element already.

    Hence elements are never removed from the internal list.

      • getByIndex

        public E getByIndex(int index)
        Gets the element at the passed index.
        Parameters:
        index - the index to look up.
        Returns:
        the element at position index or null if the index is invalid. Invalid means either that the element at the specified index has been removed or that the index is not in the range of allowed indices. The range of allowed indices is [0, number of elements added to data structure minus 1].

      • getLastIndex

        public int getLastIndex()
        Gets the last index.
        Returns:
        Returns the index of the element with the highest index. The index is not guaranteed to be valid, which means that the element with the returned index can be retrieved.

      • indexOf

        public int indexOf(java.lang.Object o)
        Get the index of the passed element.
        Parameters:
        o - element to search for
        Returns:
        the index of the specified element or -1 if the IndexAwareSet does not contain the element
